title: For Sale:  Bryco/Jennings J-22 with lots of extras
postcontent:
I bought this from a buddy of mine to teach my wife how to shoot, but it turns out she hates loud noises and is even scared of this little thing, so I figure I'll get my money back or swap it for .38 Special ammo.

Yes, it is a Jennings J-22, and we all know those pistols are not high end firearms and many are jam-o-matic pieces of crap, but this is one of the good ones.  I put 100 rounds of mixed ammunition through it with minimal problems.  It likes CCI Stingers the best and will eat them all day.  CCI Mini Mags also run well in this pistol.  Had a few jams with American Eagle.  Did not try cheap bulk ammo as unjacketed standard velocity rounds do not run well in these pistols.  Feed ramp, firing pin, extractor claw, and mags are all in great shape.  As far as J-22s go, this one is reliable and should last a lifetime.  The J-22s are decent guns with a solid following, later versions by Calwestco and Jimenez were not as reliable, and higher caliber versions in .380 had a well deserved bad reputation.  This is an early Bryco done on the original Jennings tooling with the pirate logo on the slide.

Pistol is black with black grips.  Has the improved safety switch.  Finish is in nice shape, a small bit of discoloration on the grips from solvent.  I'd rate it 90% overall.

Pistol comes with lots of extras!  8 magazines total, and they're all good ones.  Magazines only hold 6 rounds -- don't try to force a 7th one in or you'll damage the spring.  Extra firing pin, fp spring, and takedown button.  A leather belt holster.  Also have a set of old style wood grips that will need to be filed down to accommodate the new style safety, which I intended to do but never got around to it.

This is a GREAT plinker and fun gun for shooting cans up in the mountains, or a nice beater for your tacklebox.  It is not a target pistol and I would not recommend it for protection, although it is really tiny and will easily fit in a pocket.  Due to the SA striker firing system, these guns (and others like it, such as the Colt Vest Pocket or Baby Browning) should not be carried or stored with a round chambered.  This is a nice little plinker for someone.

You need to be over 21 and not a dirtbag.  Will need to see a CO DL to verify age and residency.  Thanks.

Price of 140 is pretty firm considering all the extras.  Will do a full or partial trade for good quality .38 Special ammo.

File photo attached.

title: For Sale:  USGI PVS-14 3X Magnifier
postcontent:
The USGI 3X Magnifier is a high performance Galilean Afocal Telescopic lens that easily attaches to the objective lens of many night vision devices. The 3X Magnifier screws into the internal threads of the PVS-14 or PVS-7 objective lens or snaps onto the objective of the MUM when coupled with the MUM/ MiNi-14 Magnifier Adapter.

The USGI 3X Magnifier is a great accessory that increases the versatility of your night vision monocular. We recommend using the magnifier when the monocular is employed in a weapon-mounted or hand-held surveillance mode. It can be run while head-mounted, but we do not recommend this for several reasons. First, trying to negotiate terrain while maintaining situational awareness with a magnified night vision optic on your head is difficult at best and dangerous at worst. Secondly, the added weight and cantilevered distance will more quickly fatigue your neck and back. However, the 3X Magnifier excels in its other roles and should be a staple accessory for anyone employing a night vision monocular
